The paper deals with logical and computational aspects of Constraint Satisfaction Problems (CSPs) and Datalog Programs, which are typically studied in the areas of logic (cs.LO), databases (cs.DB), computational complexity (cs.CC), data structures (cs.DS), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper's focus on bounded path duality and its implications for the computational complexity of CSPs suggests that cs.LO and cs.CC are the most likely sub-categories. However, the paper's use of Datalog Programs and its connections to structures of bounded pathwidth also make cs.DB and cs.DS likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper's relevance to AI applications of CSPs suggests that cs.AI is also a possible sub-category.
